<paragraph id="7998E42E6F32AF625DA7B17F7434E625" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Diagnose.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9FFC746CFC112ADB0E2012FBB1DC395A" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName id="79132A4F73EE347FC019B6053A62A3EA" authorityName="Padua &amp; Saeaeksjaervi" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Polysphincta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polysphincta teresa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="teresa">
<emphasis id="7B022DD1FAF0C97D1ADF86EF94EE2E3D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Polysphincta teresa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="55B137F276BE8BE88DBFEE809FA7C052" genus="P." lsidName="P. dizardi" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="dizardi">
<emphasis id="F94211958E2876BE24A83EBB086B6EE4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">P. dizardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group by the combination of the following characters: (1) epomia present, about 0.9-1.0 times length of proximal mandibular width (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4B262137A0278BED4748FA1055E61B5E" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Polysphincta teresa sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head, dorsal view F shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550751" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">10B</figureCitation>
); (2) malar space 0.4-0.6 times as long as proximal mandibular width (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="24CD41B0E08C2CEC140110A2A651D464" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Polysphincta teresa sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head, dorsal view F shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550751" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">10B</figureCitation>
); (3) fore wing with vein 1 
<emphasis id="5DC998DC99988AEBB620E0659BFD9BF7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">cu-a</emphasis>
postfurcal relative to 
<emphasis id="66210FD2C041CAF4DBAF1BFDCB02D789" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">M&amp;RS</emphasis>
(0.25-0.35 times its own length) or 1 
<emphasis id="24D8C98BAAB36F98CC7408D1F255AE1C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">cu-a</emphasis>
more or less interstitial relative to 
<emphasis id="CAE4AA918FCF7864437EFF91A3004EDD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">M&amp;RS</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="72FA36E12DD29F1407EC366B3C2B6902" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Polysphincta teresa sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head, dorsal view F shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550751" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">10A</figureCitation>
); (4) mesosoma orange, except posterior carinae of propodeum darkish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="81AA40598C776557AEB15AECE3668C6C" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Polysphincta teresa sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head, dorsal view F shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550751" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">10A</figureCitation>
); (5) fore wing hyaline (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E79311394732596EC11586C7DCDAD1ED" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Polysphincta teresa sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head, dorsal view F shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550751" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">10A</figureCitation>
); (6) hind leg whitish with proximal region of trochanter, longitudinal spot in subdistal region of inner and outer margin of femur, distal part of tibia and first tarsal segment distally and remaining tarsal segments brownish (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1DABD7B10C3CD2F35E348803AB647925" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Polysphincta teresa sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head, dorsal view F shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550751" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">10A</figureCitation>
); (7) metasoma darkish brown, with posterior margins of tergites II-V narrowly black (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F1DE187505A46C804FC54A36ACC2214C" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Polysphincta teresa sp. nov., ♀, holotype A habitus, lateral view B head and pronotum, lateral view C habitus, dorsal view D face, anterior view E head, dorsal view F shelf-like projection, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550751" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">10A, C</figureCitation>
); (8) ovipositor slightly slender, [1.7] 1.4-1.7 times as long as hind tibia.
</paragraph>
<caption id="05A3F995477B8FB55767B01E32B5CC09" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1041.65407.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550751" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" start="Figure 10" startId="F10">
